summary:
The Security Council, recalling its previous resolutions on Libya, including 1970 (2011), 2259 (2015), 2510 (2020), 2542 (2020), and 2570 (2021), and its determination that the situation in Libya remains a threat to international peace and security, 
Decides to extend the mandate of the United Nations Support Mission in Libya until 31 January 2022; 
Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
